  "text": "The question for classification research becomes the degree to which the classification is influenced politically by its domain rather than empirically representing scholarship. [CITATION_1] suggests the political disciplinarity is a result of social epistemological forces. But if the goal of the repository is to properly represent scholarship a more empirical basis for the structure of the classification would be appropriate. The absence of information science and the misnaming and misplacing of librarianship suggests political cultural pervasiveness [CITATION_2] as a form of unseen objective disciplinary violence (Tennis 2013) .",
